{"id":4525,"date":"2024-03-04T10:21:01","date_gmt":"2024-03-04T10:21:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/?p=4525"},"modified":"2024-03-04T10:21:01","modified_gmt":"2024-03-04T10:21:01","slug":"data-science-after-bca","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-science-after-bca\/","title":{"rendered":"Data Science After BCA- Jobs, Scope, Salary In India"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><p>Table of Contents<\/p><nav><ul><li ><a href=\"#data-science-after-bca\">Data Science After BCA<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#what-is-data-science\">What is Data Science?<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#skills-required-for-data-scientist\">Skills Required For Data Scientist<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#eligibility-criteria-for-data-scientist\">Eligibility Criteria for Data Scientist <\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#colleges-offering-data-science\">Colleges Offering Data Science<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#how-to-become-a-data-scientist-after-bca\">How To Become a Data Scientist After BCA<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#data-scientist-jobs\">Data Scientist Jobs<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#salary-provided-for-data-scientist\">Salary Provided For Data Scientist <\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#scope-of-data-scientist\">Scope of Data Scientist<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"data-science-after-bca\">Data Science After BCA<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing Data Science after BCA is like stepping into a tech adventure where you learn to analyze information in a super-smart way. With your BCA background, Data Science adds cool skills to help you make sense of big data and make clever decisions in the tech world. This article discusses the job, scope, and salary in data science after BCA.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-data-science\">What is Data Science?<\/h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"4883\" height=\"3255\" src=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/pexels-tima-miroshnichenko-7567486-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5874\" style=\"width:524px;height:auto\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-science-eligibility-criteria\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"5620\">Data Science<\/a> is a field that uses scientific methods to extract valuable insights from different types of data, whether it&#8217;s organized, structured, or not. The goal is to gain important business insights by studying and analyzing large volumes of data, combining techniques from mathematics, statistics, artificial intelligence, and computer engineering.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data Scientists are skilled professionals who work with massive sets of both structured and unstructured data. They process, model, and analyze this data to develop practical plans for businesses and other organizations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p> Data Scientists are experts at identifying patterns in messy, unorganized data from various sources like smart devices, social media, and emails that don&#8217;t neatly fit into a database.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"skills-required-for-data-scientist\"><strong>Skills Required For Data Scientist<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Eligibility<\/td><td>To become a Data Scientist,  a  Candidate must complete 10+2 from a recognized board with a minimum aggregate score of 50% or above with&nbsp;Mathematics, Computer Science, or Statistics as one of the main subjects.&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Employment Opportunities<\/td><td>Data Architect, Data Administrator, Business Intelligence Manager, Data Scientist,&nbsp;Data Analyst<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Required Skills<\/td><td>Data Visualization, Programming, Data Wrangling, Deep Learning, Machine Learning<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Starting Salary<\/td><td>INR 5.75 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Average Salary&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 11.44 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Highest Salary<\/td><td>INR 34 LPA &amp; above<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"eligibility-criteria-for-data-scientist\">Eligibility Criteria for Data Scientist <\/h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"6187\" height=\"4125\" src=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/pexels-anna-nekrashevich-6801648-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5918\" style=\"width:535px;height:auto\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>To take a course in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-science-roles-and-responsibilities\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"5600\">data science<\/a>, candidates are required to complete 10+2 from a recognized board with a minimum aggregate of 60% or above.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates have to be class 12th pass in the science stream along with Physics, Computer Science, and Mathematics as their compulsory subjects.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates must attempt Engineering Entrance Exams&nbsp;to get into the top data science colleges in India, such as&nbsp;JEE Main, JEE Advanced, and&nbsp;GATE.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates should have undergraduate degrees in Data Science, Computer Engineering, or another relevant discipline.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates will pursue certification programs to gain relevant skills.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates must also pursue post-graduate degrees such as&nbsp;M.Sc Data Science, and M.Tech Data Science.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Candidates should have programming languages like R,&nbsp;Python, and&nbsp;SQL&nbsp;candidates can pursue certification courses specializing in programming languages.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"colleges-offering-data-science\">Colleges Offering Data Science<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><th>Name of the Colleges<\/th><th>Location<\/th><th>Average Course Fees (INR)<\/th><\/tr><tr><td>IIT Madras<\/td><td>Madras<\/td><td>1,08,000<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Loyola College<\/td><td>Chennai<\/td><td>34,000<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Vellore Institute of Technology<\/td><td>Vellore<\/td><td>89,000<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Fergusson College<\/td><td>Pune<\/td><td>23,000<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Symbiosis International University<\/td><td>Pune<\/td><td>92,000<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies<\/td><td>Mumbai<\/td><td>37,800<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Jain University<\/td><td>Bangalore<\/td><td>31,020<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Cochin University of Science and Technology<\/td><td>Kochi<\/td><td>42,711<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Manipal Academy of Higher Education<\/td><td>Manipal<\/td><td>56,234<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Indian Institute of Science Education and Research<\/td><td>Bhopal<\/td><td>70,009<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"how-to-become-a-data-scientist-after-bca\">How To Become a Data Scientist After BCA<\/h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"5760\" height=\"3840\" src=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/pexels-andrea-piacquadio-3762800-2-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5876\" style=\"width:522px;height:auto\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To become a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-scientist-salary-in-india-2023\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"1544\">Data Scientist<\/a> in 2024, it&#8217;s not always necessary to have a BTech degree; candidates with a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/courses-after-12th-computer-science\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"1371\">BCA degree<\/a> are also eligible. Here are crucial steps for BCA graduates aspiring to become Data Scientists:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Enroll in postgraduate courses like MCA Data Science, MBA Data Science, or MBA Data Analytics.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pursue certification or diploma courses in data science.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Focus on learning programming languages such as R, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-science-projects-in-python\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"4615\">Python<\/a>, Java, Hadoop, Pig, Hive, Spark, SQL, SAS, data modeling, and machine learning.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Concentrate on learning optimization, Information, and Decision Theory.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Engage in internships and attend workshops to gain both basic and advanced knowledge of a typical corporate setup.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"data-scientist-jobs\"><strong>Data Scientist Jobs<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><th>Job Profiles<\/th><th>Job Description<\/th><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-analyst-salary\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"1498\">Data Analyst<\/a><\/td><td>A Data Analyst will examine the  data to find significant customer insights and potential uses for the information. They will also advise the company&#8217;s management and other stakeholders of this information<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/business-analyst-salary\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"1096\">Business Analyst<\/a><\/td><td>Business Analysts will evaluate an organization&#8217;s performance and work with it to enhance its systems and processes. To find solutions to business challenges, they perform research and analysis. They can  assist in introducing these solutions to businesses and their customers<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Statistical Analyst<\/td><td>They will conduct statistical research, analysis, compile, and interpret statistical records and reports for research projects.<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Architect<\/td><td>Data Architects are IT specialists who will use their  knowledge of computer science and database architecture to assess and analyze an organization&#8217;s data infrastructure, create future database plans, and put into practice ways to store and manage data for both businesses and their users<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Business Intelligence Manager<\/td><td>They are required to manage a team of business analysts and programmers. Also, they have to generate insights for strategic business decisions.<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Administrator<\/td><td>Data Administrators or Database Administrators create mechanisms for storing and protecting different types of data, like financial data and customer shipping records.<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"salary-provided-for-data-scientist\">Salary Provided For Data Scientist <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><th>Job Profile<\/th><th>Average Annual Salary&nbsp;(INR)<\/th><\/tr><tr><td>Data Analyst<\/td><td>4.72 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Solutions Analyst<\/td><td>11.51 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Business Analyst<\/td><td>6.00 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Statistical Analyst<\/td><td>6.02 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Architect<\/td><td>16.20 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Business Intelligence Manager<\/td><td>17.00 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Scientist<\/td><td>9.44 L<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Administrator<\/td><td>7.96 L<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"scope-of-data-scientist\">Scope of Data Scientist<\/h2>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"5299\" height=\"3533\" src=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/pexels-andrea-piacquadio-3756679-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5880\" style=\"width:482px;height:auto\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The scope of a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/which-of-the-following-is-performed-by-data-scientist\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"2839\">Data Scientist<\/a> is vast and continues to grow rapidly as organizations across various industries recognize the importance of data-driven decision-making. Here are key aspects that highlight the scope of Data Science:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>High Demand:<\/strong> There is a significant and growing demand for Data Scientists across industries such as finance, healthcare, technology, marketing, and more.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Diverse Industries:<\/strong> Data Scientists are not limited to a particular industry. They are needed in sectors like e-commerce, healthcare, finance, sports, and government, among others.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Decision-Making Support:<\/strong> Data Scientists play a crucial role in helping organizations make informed decisions by analyzing and interpreting complex data sets.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Innovation and Research:<\/strong> Data Scientists contribute to innovation by developing and implementing new algorithms, models, and analytical approaches.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML):<\/strong> The increasing integration of AI and ML technologies further expands the scope of Data Scientists as these fields continue to evolve.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Business Strategy:<\/strong> Data Scientists often work closely with business leaders, helping them formulate strategies based on data insights and trends.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Job Diversity:<\/strong> Data Scientists can specialize in various areas such as natural language processing, and computer vision, or focus on specific industries like finance or healthcare.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Global Opportunities:<\/strong> The skills of Data Scientists are in demand globally, offering opportunities for international careers.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Continuous Learning:<\/strong> The field of Data Science is dynamic, and professionals need to stay updated with the latest tools and techniques, providing ongoing opportunities for learning and growth.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Competitive Salaries:<\/strong> Data Scientists are often well-compensated, reflecting the high demand for their specialized skills.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>As organizations increasingly rely on data to gain a competitive edge, the role of Data Scientists is expected to remain crucial, ensuring a promising and evolving scope for those in the field.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding Data Science to a BCA degree is like giving your tech skills a turbo boost, making you a pro at crunching data for smarter solutions in the digital world. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"data-science-after-bca-fa-qs\"> Data Science After BCA- FAQs<\/h2>\n\n\n<div id=\"rank-math-faq\" class=\"rank-math-block\">\n<div class=\"rank-math-list \">\n<div id=\"faq-question-1703075938868\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q1. Is data science good after BCA?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. Having a degree in data science opens up various career opportunities, and you can explore roles such as Data Scientist, Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Analyst, or Machine Learning Engineer.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1703075952298\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q2. Which BCA job has the highest salary?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. Data Scientist, Technical Support Engineer, Digital Marketing Executive, and Cybersecurity Analyst are among the highest-paying job roles after completing BCA. <\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1703075958749\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q3. What is the salary of BCA in Google?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. At Google, BCA graduates can anticipate a starting salary ranging from INR 5 to 8 LPA, depending on their specific job role and level of experience. With increasing experience and career advancement, these professionals have the potential to earn salaries reaching INR 15 to 25 LPA or even higher. <\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><br><\/h2>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Data Science After BCA Choosing Data Science after BCA is like stepping into a tech adventure where you learn to analyze information in a super-smart way. With your BCA background, Data Science adds cool skills to help you make sense of big data and make clever decisions in the tech world. This article discusses the &#8230; <a title=\"Data Science After BCA- Jobs, Scope, Salary In India\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/data-science-after-bca\/\" aria-label=\"More on Data Science After BCA- Jobs, Scope, Salary In India\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":4750,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[13,31],"tags":[811],"class_list":["post-4525","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-computer-science","category-data-science","tag-data-science-after-bca","generate-columns","tablet-grid-50","mobile-grid-100","grid-parent","grid-33"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4525"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4525"}],"